text: man--what is there not to understand in this-----simple---DEBT....so many companies have survived since 2008 financial crisis, their debt got rolled over via easy pesy 0% interest rates for so long, now higher for longer is what making this layoffs...simple.....massive corporate debt refinanciing at higher rates means very low margins, means lower earning...to protect shareholders...well they have 2 options - 1) their product price increases 2) layoffs, for price increase people have to buy their products at those higher prices, its no garentee they can find a buyer, since demand destruction is happening, companies are facing music on price increases, they can't pass on the prices anymore...so the only option left is----LAYOFF.....this thing is just starting....we will have this MUSIC for next 6 to 12 months....
